"{\"uid\": \"citizen.co.za-sport-sa-team-olympic-games-paris\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Home\\u00bbSport  ByWesley Botton  Chief sports journalist  6 minute read  20 June 2024  07:21 am  Erin Christie has been included in the SA hockey team for the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 170, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 21, \"end\": 27, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botton,_North_Yorkshire\", \"score\": 0.9011311734315588, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Botton\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botton,_North_Yorkshire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botton,_North_Yorkshire\"}, {\"begin\": 93, \"end\": 97, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erin\", \"score\": 0.9984191603544675, \"rank\": 0.000808709545007776, \"text\": \"Erin\", \"types\": [\"Q82799\", \"Q202444\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erin\"}, {\"begin\": 132, \"end\": 134, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.681878973453476e-70, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Picture: Ashley Vlotman/Gallo Images  A total of 75 athletes in nine sports have been added to South Africa's team for the Olympic Games in Paris next month.\", \"from\": 171, \"to\": 328, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 180, \"end\": 186, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashley_Abbott\", \"score\": 0.9999989253534612, \"rank\": 1.0651437650923364e-06, \"text\": \"Ashley\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashley_Abbott\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashley_Abbott\"}, {\"begin\": 195, \"end\": 200, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gallo_Record_Company\", \"score\": 0.9999999003102907, \"rank\": 9.949739954542454e-08, \"text\": \"Gallo\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q18127\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gallo_Record_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gallo_Record_Company\"}, {\"begin\": 266, \"end\": 278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.50874947774816e-31, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 311, \"end\": 316, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1404448179296765e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After unveiling aninitial group of 39 athleteslast month, the latest\\u00a0additions announced by the SA Sports Confederation and Olympic Committee (Sascoc) on Wednesday night have increased the size of the provisional national team to 114 athletes in 15 codes, with one more squad announcement still to be made.\", \"from\": 330, \"to\": 636, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 426, \"end\": 428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.681878973453476e-70, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ALSO READ:Team SA kit unveiled for Paris Olympics  Seven athletes have been added to the athletics squad, which now consists of 24 individuals.\", \"from\": 638, \"to\": 781, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 653, \"end\": 655, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.681878973453476e-70, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 673, \"end\": 687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Along with five sprinters who have boosted the men's 4x100m and 4x400m relay teams, the squad's new additions also includemarathon runner Elroy Gelantand discus thrower Francois Prinsloo.\", \"from\": 782, \"to\": 969, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The three-member triathlon team includes former Olympic bronze medallist Henri Schoeman, while the seven-strong cycling team features experienced road specialist Ashleigh Moolman Pasio and cross country riders Alan Hatherley and Candice Lill.\", \"from\": 971, \"to\": 1213, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1044, \"end\": 1058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henri_Schoeman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Henri Schoeman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henri_Schoeman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Henri_Schoeman\"}, {\"begin\": 1133, \"end\": 1149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashleigh_Moolman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ashleigh Moolman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashleigh_Moolman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashleigh_Moolman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's pair of John Smith (a former gold medallist in the men's four) and Christopher Baxter will represent the country in rowing.\", \"from\": 1215, \"to\": 1348, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1233, \"end\": 1243, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Smith_(explorer)\", \"score\": 0.7271469534497925, \"rank\": 0.2756449933546725, \"text\": \"John Smith\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Smith_(explorer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Smith_(explorer)\"}, {\"begin\": 1304, \"end\": 1310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baxter_International\", \"score\": 0.9970625056526002, \"rank\": 0.002946133688169343, \"text\": \"Baxter\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baxter_International\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Baxter_International\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In team sports, the provisional SA women's rugby sevens squad\\u00a0features 16 athletes (a final team will be announced before the end of June), while 32 players have been confirmed in the men's and women's hockey sides.\", \"from\": 1350, \"to\": 1565, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1382, \"end\": 1384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.681878973453476e-70, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other athletes were also added to the national team for theParis Gamesin archery, badminton and fencing,\\u00a0and a total of six reserves were included in athletics and hockey.\", \"from\": 1567, \"to\": 1738, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A final group of athletes is expected to be announced later this month in various sports, such as golf, judo, rowing and skateboarding.\", \"from\": 1740, \"to\": 1875, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes and teams can also still qualify for the quadrennial showpiece in multiple other codes, including men's rugby sevens, breakdancing and beach volleyball.\", \"from\": 1877, \"to\": 2038, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Men:Akani Simbine (100m, 4x100m), Shaun Maswanganyi (200m, 4x100m), Luxolo Adams (200m), Benjamin Richardson (200m, 4x100m),\\u00a0Bayanda Walaza (4x100m), Bradley Nkoana (4x100m), Wayde van Niekerk (400m, 4x400m), Zakhiti Nene (400m, 4x400m), Lythe Pillay (400m, 4x400m), Gardeo Isaacs (4x400m), Antonie Nortje (4x400m), Tshepo Tshite (1500m), Adriaan Wildschutt (5000m, 10000m), Stephen Mokoka (marathon), Elroy Galant (marathon), Jovan van Vuuren (long jump),\\u00a0Francois Prinsloo (discus)Reserves:Sinesipho Dambile, Adrian Swart  Women:Marione Fourie (100m hurdles), Prudence Sekgodiso (800m), Zeney Geldenhuys (400m hurdles), Rogail Joseph (400m hurdles), Gerda Steyn (marathon), Cian Oldknow (marathon), Irvette van Zyl (marathon)  Men:Wian Roux (recurve)  Women:Johanita Scholtz  Men:Andrew Birkett (kayak sprint), Hamish Lovemore (kayak sprint)  Women:Tiffany Koch (kayak sprint), Esti Olivier (kayak sprint)  Women:Caitlin Rooskrantz (artistic)  Men:Ryan Gibbons (road), Jean Spies (track), Alan Hatherley (MTB)  Women:Ashleigh Moolman-Pasio (road), Tiffany Keep (road), Candice Lill (MTB), Miyanda Maseti (BMX)  Men:Harry Saner (epee)  Women:Caitlin Rooskrantz (artistic)  Men:Daniel Bell, Dayaan Cassiem, Mustapha Cassiem, Calvin Davis, Matthew Guise-Brown, Andrew Hobson, Keenan Horne, Gowan Jones, Ryan Julius, Tevin Kok, Zenani Kraai, Samkelo Mvimbi, Nqobile Ntuli, Bradley Sherwood, Nicholas Spooner, Jacques van Tonder  Reserves:Hendrik Kriek, Nduduza (Peabo) Lembethe  Women:Taheera Augousti, Quanita Bobbs, Stephanie Botha, Dirkie Chamberlain, Erin Christie, Kayla de Waal, Paris-Gail Isaacs, Marie Antoinette Louw, Ongeziwe Mali, Ntsopa Mokoena, Edith Molikoe, Kristen Paton, Hannah Pearce, Celia Seerane, Anelle van Deventer, Onthatile Zulu  Reserves:Aphiwe Dimba, Kayla Swarts  Men:John Smith (pair), Christopher Baxter (pair)  Women:Liske Lategan, Ayanda Malinga, Shona-Leah Weston, Kemisetso Baloyi, Zintle Mpupha, Sizophila Solontsi, Mathrin Simmers, Nadine Roos, Elizabeth Janse van Rensburg, Veroeshka Grain, Marlize de Bruin, Maria Tshiremba, Byrhabdre Dolf, Shiniqwa Lamprecht, Zandile Masuku, Eloise Web  Men:Joshua Bruyns (speed climbing), Mel Janse van Rensburg (lead & boulder)  Women:Aniya Holder (speed climbing), Lauren Mukheiber 